            <TABLE ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22" SEMANTIC="DATA-ID">
              <SHORT-NAME>TA_S22</SHORT-NAME>
              <LONG-NAME>DIDs Readable</LONG-NAME>
              <KEY-DOP-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_Datas_Format.ESD.Datas_Format.DOP.IDE_2B_ByteField_None" DOCREF="Alliance_Datas_Format" DOCTYPE="CONTAINER" />
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F010">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F010</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>programmingOperationFingerPrint (F010)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                    <u>Needs</u>: The FingerPrint is used by the ECU using the Security Access for the reprogramming process or write secure DID.
                    <br />
                    <br /><b>RuleReference_Fingerprint_000_b</b>
                    <br />The <b>Fingerprint</b> shall be implemented by all ECU which implement the specification Standard Security Access :
                    <br />[RENAULT] 36-00-030
                    <br />[NISSAN] 25953NDS35
                </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F010</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F010" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F011">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F011</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>IndexSrvData (F011)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                        <u>Needs</u>: The IndexSrvData is one of information which been used by the offboard tools to unlock the ECU.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_IndexSrvData_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>IndexSrvData</b> shall be implemented by all ECU which implement the specification Standard Security Access :
                        <br />[RENAULT] 36-00-030
                        <br />[NISSAN] 25953NDS35
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F011</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F011" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F012">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F012</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>Operationnal reference (F012)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>The operational reference shall correspond to ECU final state. To simplify, the operational reference equals to the pdx file reference, which will be download in plant or in after sale.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_OperationnalReference_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>OperationnalReference</b> (<b>F0.12</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F012</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F012" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F013">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F013</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>Secondary operational reference (F013)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>The secondary operational reference shall correspond to second ECU software. To simplify, the secondary operational reference equals to the secondary software file reference delivered by supplier. This file, of the secondary software, will be downloading only in after sale. This file will be a &quot;zip&quot; file.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_SecondOperRef_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>SecondOperRef</b> (<b>F0.13</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan which have two independent software inside the same box which could be updated separately.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F013</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F013" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F111">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F111</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>vehicleManufacturerECUHardwareNumber_DAI (F111)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                        <b>RuleReference_VehicleManufacturerECUHardwareNumber_DAI_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>VehicleManufacturerECUHardwareNumber_DAI</b> (<b>F1.11</b>) shall be implemented ONLY by all ECU designed for Daimler.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F111</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F111" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F121">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F121</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>vehicleManufacturerECUSoftwareNumber_DAI (F121)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>This reference corresponds to the reference to the pdx file, which will be download in plant or in after sale.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_VehicleManufacturerECUSoftwareNumber_DAI_000_b</b>
                        <br />The <b>VehicleManufacturerECUSoftwareNumber_DAI</b> (<b>F1.21</b>) shall be implemented ONLY by all ECU designed for Daimler.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F121</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F121" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F180">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F180</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>BootVersion (F180)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>This information is only used by the ECU designer, if he needs it.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_BootVersion_001_b</b>
                        <br />The <b>BootVersion</b> (<b>F1.80</b>) DID shall be implemented by all Renault ECU and all Nissan ECU.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F180</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F180" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F182">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F182</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>applicationDataIdentification (F182)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>This information is only used by the ECU designer, if he needs it.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_CalibrationNumber_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>CalibrationNumber</b> (<b>F1.82</b>) DID can be implemented by all Renault ECU and all Nissan ECU, <b>IF</b> the ECU designer <b>AND</b> the supplier needs to use this information.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F182</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F182" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F187">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F187</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>vehicleManufacturerSparePartNumber (F187)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                      <b>RuleReference_vehicleManufacturerSparePartNumber_R_000_a</b>
                      <br />The <b>vehicleManufacturerSparePartNumber_R</b> (<b>F1.87</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F187</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F187" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F188">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F188</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>vehicleManufacturerECUSoftwareNumberDataIdentifier (F188)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                        <u>Renault needs</u>: This DID is used to download the right configuration in part.
                        <br />
                        <br /><u>Nissan needs</u>: This DID is used to select the right configuration data by the OEM tool. This configuration reference is written by the OEM tool in order to refer this DID after the configuration process.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_ConfigurationFileReferenceLink_000_a</b>
                        <br />For a configurable ECU, the ConfigurationFileReferenceLink (<b>F1.88</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                        <br />
                        <br /><u>Remark</u>: The ECU designer must decide if the configuration file depend on
                        <br />- The software reference
                        <br />- The calibration reference
                        <br />If it depends on the software, the DID equals to the software reference (a specific reference for the software is needed or the ordered part)
                        <br />If it depends on the calibration, the DID equals to the pdx file reference
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F188</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F188" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F18A">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F18A</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>systemSupplierIdentifier (F18A)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>The systemSupplierIdentifier shall be used to reference the system supplier name and address information.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_systemSupplierIdentifier_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>systemSupplierIdentifier</b> (<b>F1.8A</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F18A</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F18A" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F18C">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F18C</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>ECUSerialNumber (F18C)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                        <u>Remarks</u>: The ECU serial number is used for quality department in Renault and Nissan side.
                        <br />Furthermore, it is also used for functional safety department in Nissan side.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_ECUSerialNumberDataIdentifier_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>ECUSerialNumberDataIdentifier</b> (<b>F1.8C</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F18C</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F18C" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F18E">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F18E</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>vehicleManufacturerKitAssemblyPartNumber (F18E)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                        <u>Which ECU implement it</u>: If a part includes an electronic part and a mechanical part and if the OEM part designer needs to distinguish the both reference parts because the electronic part can be changed, in after sale, without change the mechanical part.
                        <br />
                        <br /><u>Remark</u>: If the reference reading by F1.87 DID or F1.A1 DID equals to reference reading by F1.8E DID, the F1.8E DID is not necessary.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F18E</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F18E" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F190">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F190</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>VIN (F190)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>To be compliant with antitheft needs and regulation, “All the UCEs (except immobilizer UCEs) must have no possibility to erase the unitary identification on memory and/or to rewrite another malicious one”, to write again the VIN, SecurityAccess service will be used.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_VIN_005_b</b>
                        <br />The <b>VIN</b> shall be implemented by all ECU in accordance with Renault/Nissan diagnostic department.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F190</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F190" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F191">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F191</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>vehicleManufacturerECUHardwareNumber (F191)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>This DID correspond to the Hardware reference ECU. It identifies the ECU hardware AND bootloader software.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_vehicleManufacturerECUHardwareNumber_000_b</b>
                        <br />The <b>vehicleManufacturerECUHardwareNumber</b> (<b>F1.91</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F191</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F191" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F194">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F194</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>systemSupplierECUSoftwareNumber (F194)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                      <u>Needs</u>: This information is only used by the ECU designer.
                      <br />
                      <br /><b>RuleReference_SystemSupplierECUsoftwareNumber_000_a</b>
                      <br />The <b>SystemSupplierECUsoftwareNumber</b> (<b>F1.94</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F194</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F194" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F195">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F195</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>systemSupplierECUSoftwareVersionNumber (F195)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>This information is only used by the ECU designer.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_SystemSupplierECUSoftwareVersionNumber_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>SystemSupplierECUSoftwareVersionNumber</b> (<b>F1.95</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F195</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F195" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F196">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F196</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>exhaustRegulationOrTypeApprovalNumberDataIdentifier (F196)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                        <b>RuleReference_exhaustRegulationOrTypeApprovalNumberDataIdentifier_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>exhaustRegulationOrTypeApprovalNumberDataIdentifier</b> shall be implemented by all OBD ECU designed for Renault and all OBD ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F196</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F196" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F197">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F197</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>SystemNameOrEngineType (F197)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>The SystemNameOrEnginType shall be used to reference the system name or engine type. This DID is only used for OBD ECU.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_SystemNameOrEngineType_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>SystemNameOrEngineType</b> shall be implemented by all OBD ECU designed for Renault and all OBD ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F197</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F197" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F1A0">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F1A0</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>diagnosticVersion (F1A0)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                        <u>Needs</u>: To identify the right reaper method, the OEM defines for each ECU a specific VDIAG. This information shall be done by OEM diagnostic team.
                        <br />
                        <br /><b>RuleReference_VDIAG_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>VDIAG</b> (<b />F1.A0<b />) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F1A0</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F1A0" />
                <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Default_Session_01" />
                  <PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.STC.Session_States.ST.Extended_Diagnostic_Session_03" />
                </PRE-CONDITION-STATE-REFS>
              </TABLE-ROW>
              <TABLE-ROW ID="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.TA.TA_S22.TR.TR_TA_S22_F1A1">
                <SHORT-NAME>TR_TA_S22_F1A1</SHORT-NAME>
                <LONG-NAME>VehicleManufacturerSparePartNumber_N (F1A1)</LONG-NAME>
                <DESC>
                  <p>
                        <b>RuleReference_vehicleManufacturerSparePartNumber_N_000_a</b>
                        <br />The <b>vehicleManufacturerSparePartNumber_N</b> (<b>F1.A1</b>) shall be implemented by all ECU designed for Renault and all ECU designed for Nissan.
                    </p>
                </DESC>
                <KEY>F1A1</KEY>
                <STRUCTURE-REF ID-REF="DLC.Alliance_ECUs_01_7_0_1.ESD.Alliance_ECUS_UDS.DOP.ST_S22_F1A1" />
